Gospel singer, Chioma Jesus has reacted to the death of her colleague and popular music minister, Osinachi Nwachukwu. DAILY POST had reported that Osinachi, known for the hit song “Ekwueme”, died on Friday night after battling with an undisclosed disease. Her death has thrown both her fans and the entire gospel music industry into mourning. However, there are reports in some quarters that she allegedly suffered domestic violence and was rushed to the hospital after her husband hit her. Reacting, Chioma Jesus revealed she’s heartbroken from the news of Osinachi’s death. Her Instagram post reads: OSI’M I’m so heartbroken and still in disbelief.” The singer’s family is yet to issue a statement on her death.